00:27:51.019 --> 00:27:55.570
And I was designing servers.
And I had these big, loud machines in my room,

00:27:55.570 --> 00:28:01.979
and I had the perfect roommates.
They never minded.

00:28:01.979 --> 00:28:08.979
So -- and the question is, I'm an engineer,
so I was curious, like, when we -- hearing

00:28:11.129 --> 00:28:16.059
people in a room want to attract attention,
we usually, like, use a glass or something

00:28:16.059 --> 00:28:20.399
to make a noise so everybody -- attract everyone's
attention.

00:28:20.399 --> 00:28:27.399
I wonder if, for people who don't hear, how
do you do that?

00:28:28.239 --> 00:28:29.039
&gt;&gt;Marlee Matlin: (Stamping foot).
&gt;&gt;&gt;Really?

00:28:29.039 --> 00:28:32.539
&gt;&gt;Marlee Matlin: No, we flash the lights.
We just flick the lights off and on or we

00:28:32.539 --> 00:28:34.850
wave.
But that's -- 'cause that's very visible.

00:28:34.850 --> 00:28:37.979
I can see it, because my peripheral vision
is very good.

00:28:37.979 --> 00:28:42.830
My eyes are the means of which I depend on
to use, just as you depend on your ears to

00:28:42.830 --> 00:28:45.549
hear and you can hear anything.
I'm very visual.

00:28:45.549 --> 00:28:50.409
If you do this (indicating) or this (indicating),
like, when there's paparazzi, a good example,

00:28:50.409 --> 00:28:53.539
when I go to paparazzi.
At first when I came into the business, they

00:28:53.539 --> 00:28:57.950
would call my name, Marlee, Marlee.
And I would stand there like, what -- Whoopi

00:28:57.950 --> 00:29:00.999
Goldberg said, "She's Deaf.
You can't yell at a Deaf woman."

00:29:00.999 --> 00:29:06.309
And then, of course, they'd do this, they'd
just make -- do pretend sign language, and

00:29:06.309 --> 00:29:07.720
then I would look, and then they'd take my
picture.

00:29:07.720 --> 00:29:11.289
And then some more pretend sign language,
and I'd look, and they'd take my picture.

00:29:11.289 --> 00:29:13.419
They've learned this.
They still do this to this day.

00:29:13.419 --> 00:29:15.820
It works.
It works for me.

00:29:15.820 --> 00:29:19.629
For you to get the attention of someone who
is Deaf, who can't hear, you just do this

00:29:19.629 --> 00:29:25.669
or tap their shoulder or -- I mean, anything
that involves hands movement or flashing the

00:29:25.669 --> 00:29:28.309
lights, that usually works.
Or throw something.

00:29:28.309 --> 00:29:28.850
&gt;&gt;&gt;Okay.

00:29:28.850 --> 00:29:32.230
&gt;&gt;Marlee Matlin: You know, spit ball that
way.

00:29:32.230 --> 00:29:37.330
&gt;&gt;&gt;Then one suggestion, and this is more
